\ul\b\fs44 Non-Functional Requirements\line\f1\rtlch\lang1037\line\f0\ltrch\fs28\lang1033 1. Performance\par
\ulnone Response Times\ul :\ulnone\b0 The system should respond to user actions (e.g., logging in, switching cameras) within \f1\rtlch\lang1037 2 \f0\ltrch\lang1033 seconds under normal load conditions\ul\b\par
\ulnone Throughput:\b0  The system must handle multiple concurrent users with minimal latency.\ul\b\par
\ulnone Resource Utilization:\b0 Optimize CPU and memory usage to ensure efficient processing of video streams and minimize costs.\ul\b\par
\ulnone Video Processing Speed\ul :\ulnone\b0 Analyze and generate drowning predictions in real-time with less than \f1\rtlch\lang1037 1\f0\ltrch\lang1033 -second delay per frame.\b\par
\ul 2. Reliability \par
\ulnone Uptime\ul :\ulnone\b0 Ensure system availability of \f1\rtlch\lang1037 99.9\f0\ltrch\lang1033 % to provide continuous monitoring and alerts.\ul\par
\ulnone\b Precentage: \b0 Make sure the system will detect silent drowning and alert with 80% accuracy.\ul\b\par
3. Security\par
\ulnone Authentication and Authorization: \b0 Implement secure authentication mechanisms \ul\b\par
\ulnone Secure Communication Protocols: \b0 Use HTTPS for all web interfaces and secure protocols (e.g., RTSP over TLS) for video streaming.\par
\ul\b 4. Data Architecture\par
\ulnone Data Storage:\b0 Requirement: Use a combination of relational and NoSQL databases to store structured data (e.g., user profiles, camera settings) and unstructured data (e.g., video metadata).\ul\b\par
\ulnone Data Models: \b0 Design scalable and efficient data models that support quick retrieval and storage of large volumes of video and event data.\par
\b Data Availability:\b0 Ensure data is accessible to authorized users at all times.\ul\b\par
5. Integration\par
\ulnone Interoperability:\b0 Ensure the system can interoperate with various camera brands and models by supporting standard protocols like RTSP.\ul\b\par
6. Maintainability and Extensibility\par
\ulnone Code Quality:\b0 Adhere to coding standards and best practices to ensure code is clean, well-documented, and maintainable.\par
\ul\b 7. User Interface\par

\pard\rtlpar\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qr\ulnone User-Friendly Interface:\b0 Design intuitive and easy-to-navigate interface for the application to enhance user experience.\line\line\line\line\line\line Use Case 2: Login\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Log into the system to access features\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: The user is registered and has valid credentials\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects the "Login" option\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system prompts for email and password\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user enters the credentials and submits\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system validates the credentials\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 If valid, the user is granted access to the dashboard\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The user is logged in and can use the system\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Use Case 3: Camera Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Sub-use Case: Add Camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Add a new camera to the system\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: The user is logged in\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects the "Camera Management" option\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user clicks "Add Camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system prompts for details such as camera name, username, password, and IP address\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user provides the details and submits\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system verifies and adds the camera to the user\f2\rquote\f0 s list\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The camera is successfully added and ready for use\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Sub-use Case: Edit Camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Edit details of an existing camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: The user has already added at least one camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user navigates to "Camera Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects an existing camera to edit\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system displays the current details of the camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user makes necessary changes and submits\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system updates the camera details\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The camera details are updated\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Sub-use Case: Delete Camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Remove a camera from the system\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: At least one camera is linked to the user\f2\rquote\f0 s account\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user navigates to "Camera Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects a camera to delete\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system asks for confirmation\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user confirms the deletion\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system removes the camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The camera is removed from the user\f2\rquote\f0 s account\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Use Case 4: Category Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Sub-use Case: Add Category\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Create a new category for organizing cameras\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: The user is logged in\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects "Category Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user clicks "Add Category\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system prompts for a category name\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user enters the name and submits\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system creates the new category\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The new category is available for use\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Sub-use Case: Edit Category\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Modify an existing category\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: The category exists\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user navigates to "Category Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects a category to edit\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system displays the current category name\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user updates the name and submits\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system updates the category\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The category is updated\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Sub-use Case: Delete Category\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Delete an unused category\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: The category exists\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user navigates to "Category Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects a category to delete\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system prompts for confirmation\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user confirms\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system deletes the category\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The category is removed\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Use Case 5: View Live Stream\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: View a live video feed from a selected camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: At least one camera is added to the system\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects "Camera Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user clicks "View Live Stream\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system fetches the live feed from the selected camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user views the live video\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The user monitors the camera feed in real-time\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Use Case 6: Receive Drowning Alerts\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User, Emergency Services\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Notify the user and emergency services of potential drowning events\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: The camera is operational and connected to the system\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system monitors the camera feed for signs of drowning using AI\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Upon detecting potential drowning, the system generates an alert\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system sends the alert to the user\f2\rquote\f0 s configured devices (e.g., phone, email)\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 If configured, the system notifies emergency services\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: Relevant parties are notified of the incident\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Use Case 7: Recording Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Sub-use Case: Access Recordings\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: View recorded video footage\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: Recordings exist in the system\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects "Recording Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user navigates to the desired date or camera\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system displays available recordings\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects a recording to view\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The recording is displayed to the user\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Sub-use Case: Manage Recordings\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Delete or update video recordings\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: Recordings exist in the system\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects "Recording Management\f1\rtlch\lang1037 ."\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects a recording to edit or delete\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system prompts for confirmation (in the case of deletion)\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user confirms, and the system updates or removes the recording\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The recording is updated or deleted\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Use Case 8: Activate Emergency Mode\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Enable all camera feeds during emergencies\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: Cameras are added and operational\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user triggers the "Activate Emergency Mode" option\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system opens all live camera feeds simultaneously\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user monitors all areas in real-time\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The user can oversee all camera feeds to respond to the emergency\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\f0\ltrch\lang1033\line\line\line Use Case 1: Register Account\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Actor(s): User\f1\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Goal: Create an account to access the system\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Preconditions: The user has not previously registered and has access to a valid email address\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Steps\f1\rtlch\lang1037 :\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user opens the SilentGuard application\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user selects the "Register Account" option\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system prompts the user to provide details such as name, email, and password\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user enters the details and submits the form\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system validates the information and sends a confirmation email\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The user verifies the email\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 The system activates the account\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 Postconditions: The user account is created and can now be used to log in\f1\rtlch\lang1037 .\ul\b\f0\ltrch\lang1033\par
